<TITLE> Indian government 'winning vote' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 India, July 22 (bdnews24.com/BBC)India's Congress party-led government is leading a vote of confidence over a civilian nuclear deal with the United States, with most votes counted. The vote came after the government's left-wing allies withdrew their support in protest at the controversial accord. The government motion has received 253 votes with 232 against, but about 50 votes are still being counted. If the government were to lose the vote, India would face early elections and the deal would be under threat. Two days of debate ended in uproar amid opposition allegations of vote buying
